6:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Frase and Peppertype share a solid foundation of core features including Long Form, Short Form, Seo Tools, Templates. Where Frase pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Api Access, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on this capability. On the other hand, Peppertype uniquely offers Tone Control and Plagiarism Check, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Frase holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 6/10, while Peppertype scores 6/10 overall and 7/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Frase offers a more budget-friendly entry point at $15/mo, compared to Peppertype's starting price of $25/mo. Peppertype stands out by offering a free plan, giving you a risk-free way to explore the platform. Frase requires a paid subscription from the start."}]]}]
