a:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Frase is best suited for SEO content, content briefs, SERP analysis, content optimization, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Peppertype, meanwhile, shines for content marketing, blog outlines, social media, ad copy, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2016, Frase describes itself as \"AI-powered SEO content optimization and research tool.\" Peppertype, established in 2020, positions itself as \"AI content marketing platform by Pepper Content.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
b:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Frase** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (7.0 vs 6.0), more competitive pricing. However, this does not mean Peppertype is a poor choice — far from it. Peppertype excels in its own right, particularly for content marketing and blog outlines.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value excellent serp analysis and content brief generation, go with Frase. If clean ui with well-organized templates matters more to you, Peppertype is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
